# skill: dev-implement
# purpose: Write actual code (RPOLES Phase 5: EXECUTE)
# triggers: Dependencies located, ready to code

## Invocation
```
dev-implement <task-id> [--outline <outline-file>] [--dependencies <deps-file>] [--file <specific-file>]
```

## Output
Creates/Modifies: Source files + tests

## Implementation Flow

### 1. Load Context
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# dev-implement.skill implementation

TASK_ID="$1"
OUTLINE_FILE="${2:-memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/outline.md}"
DEPS_FILE="${3:-memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/dependencies.md}"

if [ ! -f "$OUTLINE_FILE" ]; then
    echo "Error: Outline file not found. Run dev-outline first."
    exit 1
fi

OUTLINE=$(cat "$OUTLINE_FILE")
```

### 2. Implementation Strategy
```bash
# Process each file in outline
process_file() {
    local file="$1"
    local action="$2"

    case "$action" in
        create)
            create_file "$file"
            ;;
        modify)
            modify_file "$file"
            ;;
        delete)
            delete_file "$file"
            ;;
    esac
}

create_file() {
    local file="$1"
    local outline_section=$(extract_outline_section "$file" "$OUTLINE")

    # Create directory if needed
    mkdir -p "$(dirname "$file")"

    # Generate file content from outline
    cat > "$file" << EOF
$(generate_file_content "$file" "$outline_section")
EOF

    # Create checkpoint
    checkpoint --phase execute --description "Created $file"
}

modify_file() {
    local file="$1"
    local outline_section=$(extract_outline_section "$file" "$OUTLINE")

    if [ ! -f "$file" ]; then
        echo "Error: File not found for modification: $file"
        return 1
    fi

    # Apply changes per outline
    apply_modifications "$file" "$outline_section"

    # Create checkpoint
    checkpoint --phase execute --description "Modified $file"
}
```

### 3. Self-Review Checklist
```markdown
# Self-Review: <task-id>/<file>

## Code Quality
- [ ] Code follows existing patterns (see dependencies.md)
- [ ] Function names are descriptive
- [ ] Functions are single-purpose
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Comments explain "why", not "what"

## Functionality
- [ ] Implements all requirements from outline
- [ ] Handles edge cases
- [ ] Error handling is appropriate
- [ ] Returns correct types/values

## Testing
- [ ] Tests written alongside code
- [ ] Tests cover happy path
- [ ] Tests cover edge cases
- [ ] Tests are isolated

## Security
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Input validation present
- [ ] No obvious vulnerabilities

## Performance
- [ ] No obvious inefficiencies
- [ ] Appropriate data structures used
- [ ] No unnecessary allocations

## Documentation
- [ ] Functions have docstrings
- [ ] Complex logic is explained
- [ ] API changes documented
```

### 4. Implementation Template
```python
# Template for new Python files (adapt per language)

"""
Module: <name>
Task: $TASK_ID
Created: $(date +%Y-%m-%d)

Purpose: <from outline>
"""

# Imports (from dependencies.md)
from <module> import <class>

# Constants
CONSTANT_NAME = "value"

# Type definitions
class <TypeName>:
    """<brief description>"""

    def __init__(self, <params>):
        """Initialize <name>"""
        <initialization>

    def <method>(self, <params>) -> <return>:
        """
        <method description>

        Args:
            <param>: <description>

        Returns:
            <description>

        Raises:
            <ExceptionType>: <when>
        """
        <implementation>
```

### 5. Checkpoint
```bash
checkpoint --phase execute --description "Implementation complete for $TASK_ID" \
    --next "Run tests and proceed to dev-test"
```
